ce University majoring in computer science but with deep interests in physics. I am currently working at Rice University to recover data from partially damaged telescope data using machine learning and developing my ability to solve interdisciplinary problems in both physics and computer science. </p>\n<p>Here's a few technologies I've been working with recently:</p>"}}]},"jobs":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Undergraduate Researcher","company":"Solar Physics Research Group","location":"Houston, TX","range":"August 2019 - Present","url":"http://solar.rice.edu/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Develop machine learning algorithm (Random Forest) to recover damaged data from a telescope</li>\n<li>Verify data recovered using previous data under a similar physical condition</li>\n<li>Ensure the entirety of the data before a new telescope is deployed and make the algorithm applicable to other data recovery job</li>\n</ul>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Management Intern","company":"Polaris & Dawn Consulting","location":"Beijing, CN","range":"June - August 2019","url":"http://www.polarisanddawn.com/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Developed a course scheduling system using Python (pandas) to accelerate the workflow</li>\n<li>Used Google Map API to develop configured maps to help customers understand different school</li>\n<li>Proposed and implemented the automated scheduling and feedback system between consultants, teachers and clients and saved 10 hours/week of manual work</li>\n</ul>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Undergraduate Research Assistant","company":"T.W.Bonner Nuclear Laboratory","location":"Houston, TX","range":"May - July 2017","url":"http://bonnerlab.rice.edu/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Used machine learning methods and high energy physics tools like ROOT and TMVA under Linux enviroment analyze particle collision data with C++.</li>\n<li>Collaborated with <a href=\"http://wl33.web.rice.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Prof. Wei Li</a> and more than 3000 collaborators on LHC project on high energy physics research.</li>\n</ul>"}}]},"featured":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Deeplearning.ai","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='400'%20height='265'%3e%3cpath%20d='M21%2012v11l4-4C37%205%2059%204%2073%2017l5%206V0H21v12m104%201c-18%209-21%2029-7%2041%2019%2016%2049%200%2044-23-3-16-23-25-37-18m19%207c7%207-1%2018-10%2017-7-2-11-9-7-16%200-2%200-2-2-1-3%203-4%208-2%2013%206%2012%2026%208%2026-5%200-4-3-10-5-10v2m7%201l2%203c5%2010-5%2023-17%2023-13%200-22-13-17-23l1-3c-1%200-2%201-2%203-6%2014%207%2029%2022%2026%2011-2%2018-13%2015-23-1-4-4-8-4-6M32%2039c-2%203%200%204%208%204%205%200%208-1%209-2l2-1v2l3%201%203-1v-1l3%201c1%201%201%201%201-1h1c2%203%206%203%206%200s0-3-7-3c-4%200-6%201-7%202h-1c0-3-7-2-8%200s-1%202-1%200c-1-2-6-2-8%200-1%202-2%202-2%201v-1l1-1h-3m42%2024c-11%2014-35%2014-48%201l-4-4v24H5v7l1%207h16v12c0%2011%200%2011%202%2012l28%207%2026%207V98h16V84H78V59l-4%204'%20fill='%2364ffda'%20fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":1.5102685624012637,"src":"/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/e8606/deeplearning.png","srcSet":"/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/53aff/deeplearning.png 175w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/1844f/deeplearning.png 350w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/e8606/deeplearning.png 700w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/c9f12/deeplearning.png 1050w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/ea5f8/deeplearning.png 1400w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/7cfd2/deeplearning.png 1912w","srcWebp":"/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/93ec8/deeplearning.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/61503/deeplearning.webp 175w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/850cb/deeplearning.webp 350w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/93ec8/deeplearning.webp 700w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/fbd0c/deeplearning.webp 1050w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/f0780/deeplearning.webp 1400w,\n/static/c6259660673f253a0074bfbf35b4349c/079ae/deeplearning.webp 1912w","sizes":"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"}}},"tech":["TensorFlow","Jupyter Notebook","Python"],"github":"","external":"","show":"true"},"html":"<p>I implemented CNN to detect object (face and car) and style transfer with and without Tensorflow. I also implemented RNN (LSTM) to improvise Jazz and translate text</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Heavy Ion Research","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='400'%20height='210'%3e%3cpath%20d='M75%2092v2h89v-5H75v3'%20fill='%2364ffda'%20fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":1.9044368600682593,"src":"/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/e8606/heavy.png","srcSet":"/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/53aff/heavy.png 175w,\n/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/1844f/heavy.png 350w,\n/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/e8606/heavy.png 700w,\n/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/c9f12/heavy.png 1050w,\n/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/68480/heavy.png 1116w","srcWebp":"/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/93ec8/heavy.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/61503/heavy.webp 175w,\n/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/850cb/heavy.webp 350w,\n/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/93ec8/heavy.webp 700w,\n/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/fbd0c/heavy.webp 1050w,\n/static/72d7b7b319f31e7558ba33ba57bed5cd/fbc49/heavy.webp 1116w","sizes":"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"}}},"tech":["ROOT","TMVA","C++"],"github":"","external":"https://zxqlxy.synology.me:5001/d/f/438834080071553799","show":"true"},"html":"<p>• Analyzed the data of tens of millions of collisions of J/psi mesons and strange charm mesons collected from <a href=\"https://home.cern/science/accelerators/large-hadron-collider\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">LHC</a></p>\n<p>• Used boost decision tree, rectangular cut and MLP to train the data to get a better selection of the signal through <a href=\"http://tmva.sourceforge.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">TMVA</a></p>\n<p>• Manipulated data stored in trees and visualized them via <a href=\"https://root.cern.ch/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">ROOT</a></p>\n<p>• Optimized the C++ software in the Linux environment and increased the signal significance by 200%</p>\n<p>P.S. The external link is to a presentation of the research result</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Google MAP API Configure Maps","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='400'%20height='215'%3e%3cpath%20d='M200%20162v53h100a756%20756%200%200084-2h-2l-2%201v-1c1-1%200-1-3-1l-5%201-2%201-2-1-2-1-3%201-1%201v-1l-1-1-2%201h-1l-5-1c-3%200-4%200-3%201v1l-2-1c0-2%204-2%2026-2h26V108H200v54m4-51l-1%205v5h41l5%201v-11l-22-1-23%201m183%205v5h11v-10l-6-1h-5v6m0%2055v6h11v-10l-6-1h-5v5m0%2026v11h11v-22h-11v11'%20fill='%2364ffda'%20fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":1.8620253164556961,"src":"/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/e8606/google.png","srcSet":"/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/53aff/google.png 175w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/1844f/google.png 350w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/e8606/google.png 700w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/c9f12/google.png 1050w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/ea5f8/google.png 1400w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/6a46e/google.png 2942w","srcWebp":"/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/93ec8/google.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/61503/google.webp 175w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/850cb/google.webp 350w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/93ec8/google.webp 700w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/fbd0c/google.webp 1050w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/f0780/google.webp 1400w,\n/static/c0bb41a2525072772e66ec25c23ed3c2/a0871/google.webp 2942w","sizes":"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"}}},"tech":["JavaScript","Html","CSS"],"github":"","external":"https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/77326579","show":"true"},"html":"<p>I self-learned Google Map API to configure maps for Polaris &#x26; Dawn Consulting for clients. (Note: the external link is in chinese about the tutorial for this configuration)</p>"}}]},"projects":{"edges":[]},"extracurriculars":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Guid of International Young Physicsts Tournament","image":"","tech":[null],"github":"","external":"https://iypt.org/","show":"true"},"html":"<p>• Communicated with team Georgia to take care of their living and communication with the Tournament for 7 days</p>\n<p>• Provided technical and empirical help to teams in competition and helped the organizers to coordinate schedule and venue</p>"}}]},"contact":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Get In Touch"},"html":"<p>Although a physics and computer science major, I am also interested in photography, movies, art, traveling and fortune telling. In the processes of puesuing my interests, I get to know a lot more interesting people.</p>\n<p>So,  If you want to ask me anything or simply say Hi, I will respond!</p>"}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":true}}}